               Vertue passing.
               This world hath naught that worthy is
               Why longer we should lyue,
               Except those graces we respect,
               Whiche vertue sole doth giue.
            
            
               Faith.
               Let vs kepe close our faith in hart,
               Nor vauntingly it sell,
               
                  The one is easy washd away,
               The other long doth dwell.
            
            
               The meane.
               Be not to iust, be not to wyse,
               Extreames of all thinges flye,
               Shunne both extreames, and that persue
